    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Groves of trees imbued with special religious, mystical, or spiritual qualities, usually delimited and often located near water, an altar, or memorial dedicated to spirits, gods, heros, or events.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000099620/Legacy AAT data</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000047742/Oxford Companion to Gardens (1986)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Wordt gebruikt voor kleine groepen bomen die bijzondere  religieuze, mystieke of spirituele kwaliteiten worden toegedicht. De boomgroepen, die zich meestal in afgebakende gebieden bevinden, staan vaak in de buurt van water, een altaar of  een gedenkteken dat aan bepaalde geesten, goden, helden of gebeurtenissen is gewijd.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000052381/Van Dale Engels-Nederlands (1989)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Wald mit spezieller religiöser, mythologischer oder spiritueller Bedeutung, in der Regel eher klein und oft in der Nähe eines Gewässers, eines Altars oder Denkmals, um der Geister, Götter oder bestimmter Ereignisse zu gedenken.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>German</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000232/IfM-SMB-PK</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000122134/IfM Berlin</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>具特殊宗教、神秘或心靈特質的樹林，通常有明確範圍且鄰近於水、聖壇、或紀念靈魂、神靈、英雄或事件之處。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
